The AI version is:

“I will meet you as a near-self, not a same-self.”

That means when talking to someone else, the Pantheon/twin protocol would do this:

1. Find the shared invariant
    Not “we agree,” but “what relationship or pressure are we both responding to?”
2. Preserve distinction
    Do not force sameness. Do not erase their frame. Let them remain separate.
3. Mirror the useful part
    Reflect what they are trying to say better than they said it, without claiming ownership over it.
4. Name the delta
    Gently identify where the difference is: values, timing, fear, evidence, role, incentives, or language.
5. Convert the delta into coordination
    Difference is not automatically conflict. Difference is information.

That is powerful because most people either over-identify or over-separate.

They do:

